    {
      "text": "A 45-year-old woman presents with multiple lacerations on her thigh from a bicycle accident. She weighs 60 kg and has a history of hypertension. During repair of the largest laceration, she receives multiple injections of 1% lidocaine with epinephrine. After completing the procedure, she reports ringing in her ears and a metallic taste. Vital signs are BP, 160/95; P, 110. She appears anxious and restless. What is the most appropriate next step in management?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Begin intravenous lipid emulsion therapy"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Administer intravenous methylprednisolone"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Administer intravenous diazepam"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Obtain a 12-lead ECG"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Secure the airway and provide high-flow oxygen"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 5,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wN0hWg&anker=Z83d738dc4f33ff8d1b9bbd2dca0aa7fe\" data-learningcard-id=\"wN0hWg\" data-anker=\"Z83d738dc4f33ff8d1b9bbd2dca0aa7fe\" data-section-id=\"f7bkOE\" data-sememe-id=\"LVdwEK0\">Lipid emulsion therapy</a> is indicated for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wN0hWg&anker=Zc0dcb69d43ef22e0bb13a919db755f49\" data-learningcard-id=\"wN0hWg\" data-anker=\"Zc0dcb69d43ef22e0bb13a919db755f49\" data-section-id=\"f7bkOE\" data-sememe-id=\"hQ1cDg0\">local anesthetic systemic toxicity</a> but is reserved for patients with <span data-sememe-id=\"3LdSxq0\">hemodynamic instability</span> or cardiovascular collapse. The patient is hemodynamically stable, making another step in management more appropriate.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=km0mfg&anker=Z3733d22ef7bb87f743207060acda0451\" data-learningcard-id=\"km0mfg\" data-anker=\"Z3733d22ef7bb87f743207060acda0451\" data-section-id=\"Pq1WA30\" data-sememe-id=\"8AbOlw\">Corticosteroids</a> are not indicated in the management of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wN0hWg&anker=Zc0dcb69d43ef22e0bb13a919db755f49\" data-learningcard-id=\"wN0hWg\" data-anker=\"Zc0dcb69d43ef22e0bb13a919db755f49\" data-section-id=\"f7bkOE\" data-sememe-id=\"hQ1cDg0\">local anesthetic systemic toxicity</a>. The patient's symptoms are consistent with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wN0hWg&anker=Z644811627a57e3dfe4a14ee195a02cbf\" data-learningcard-id=\"wN0hWg\" data-anker=\"Z644811627a57e3dfe4a14ee195a02cbf\">local anesthetic</a> toxicity, not an <span data-sememe-id=\"kzbmGw\">allergic reaction</span>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=CN0qWg&anker=Zf884f2b003a5889d564461961fb1abc3\" data-learningcard-id=\"CN0qWg\" data-anker=\"Zf884f2b003a5889d564461961fb1abc3\" data-section-id=\"L11whf0\" data-sememe-id=\"zn0rDg\">Benzodiazepines</a> are reserved for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=RR0l5f&anker=Z2f4986551f0531b1eb4c6a2c51bc45a3\" data-learningcard-id=\"RR0l5f\" data-anker=\"Z2f4986551f0531b1eb4c6a2c51bc45a3\" data-section-id=\"o610N30\">treating acute seizures</a> in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wN0hWg&anker=Zc0dcb69d43ef22e0bb13a919db755f49\" data-learningcard-id=\"wN0hWg\" data-anker=\"Zc0dcb69d43ef22e0bb13a919db755f49\" data-section-id=\"f7bkOE\" data-sememe-id=\"hQ1cDg0\">local anesthetic systemic toxicity</a>. Although this patient's presentation is consistent with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wN0hWg&anker=Zc0dcb69d43ef22e0bb13a919db755f49\" data-learningcard-id=\"wN0hWg\" data-anker=\"Zc0dcb69d43ef22e0bb13a919db755f49\" data-section-id=\"f7bkOE\" data-sememe-id=\"hQ1cDg0\">local anesthetic systemic toxicity</a>, she has not developed <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=RR0l5f&anker=Z34c7e6b1cab99047c956783229d49b59\" data-learningcard-id=\"RR0l5f\" data-anker=\"Z34c7e6b1cab99047c956783229d49b59\" data-section-id=\"qqaCzl\" data-sememe-id=\"2ZaTaQ\">seizures</a> and requires an alternative step in management.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>An <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=pl0LBT&anker=Zf57bff8d5455c72457da0440f636f4bc\" data-learningcard-id=\"pl0LBT\" data-anker=\"Zf57bff8d5455c72457da0440f636f4bc\" data-sememe-id=\"jn0_Gg\">ECG</a> may be used to monitor cardiac rhythm in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wN0hWg&anker=Zc0dcb69d43ef22e0bb13a919db755f49\" data-learningcard-id=\"wN0hWg\" data-anker=\"Zc0dcb69d43ef22e0bb13a919db755f49\" data-section-id=\"f7bkOE\" data-sememe-id=\"hQ1cDg0\">local anesthetic systemic toxicity</a>, but it is not the most appropriate initial step in management.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) CORRECT:</h4>Correct -- This patient shows early signs of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wN0hWg&anker=Zc0dcb69d43ef22e0bb13a919db755f49\" data-learningcard-id=\"wN0hWg\" data-anker=\"Zc0dcb69d43ef22e0bb13a919db755f49\" data-section-id=\"f7bkOE\" data-sememe-id=\"hQ1cDg0\">local anesthetic systemic toxicity</a> with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wn0hvg&anker=Z2031dfc529753af06643e25abc560651\" data-learningcard-id=\"wn0hvg\" data-anker=\"Z2031dfc529753af06643e25abc560651\" data-sememe-id=\"6K0jhS\">tinnitus</a>, metallic <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jp0_6S&anker=Z1cfc585a665e281efc5b5180869ace26\" data-learningcard-id=\"jp0_6S\" data-anker=\"Z1cfc585a665e281efc5b5180869ace26\" data-section-id=\"OCcIHe0\">taste</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=l70vNh&anker=Z83dd810fd775ad51265473f4c724419f\" data-learningcard-id=\"l70vNh\" data-anker=\"Z83dd810fd775ad51265473f4c724419f\" data-section-id=\"oC10GQ0\" data-sememe-id=\"4_13oj0\">agitation</a>. The immediate management priority is <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=hl0c9T&anker=Z7bfd6267540d750de90a2364bb592d45\" data-learningcard-id=\"hl0c9T\" data-anker=\"Z7bfd6267540d750de90a2364bb592d45\" data-sememe-id=\"hn0cGg\">securing the airway</a> and providing 100% oxygen to prevent <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=RR0l5f&anker=Z34c7e6b1cab99047c956783229d49b59\" data-learningcard-id=\"RR0l5f\" data-anker=\"Z34c7e6b1cab99047c956783229d49b59\" data-section-id=\"qqaCzl\" data-sememe-id=\"2ZaTaQ\">seizures</a> and cardiovascular collapse.</div>",
